===Origin===
[[File:Cullen Bloodstone (Earth-616) from Avengers Arena Vol 1 5 001.jpg|250px|left|thumb|The faculty of the Braddock Academy trying to subdue Cullen in his monster form]]
The Braddock Academy was organized under the direction of [[Brian Braddock (Earth-616)|Captain Britain]] in his ancestral home, [[Braddock Manor]] in [[England]]. Much like the [[America]]n [[Xavier's School for Gifted Youngsters|Jean Grey School for Higher Learning]] or the [[Avengers Academy (Earth-616)|Avengers Academy]], the Braddock Academy is tasked with training [[Britain]]'s best and brightest children to become new generations of heroes.{{r|Avengers Arena #5}}

===Murderworld===
[[File:Braddock Academy (Earth-616) from Avengers Arena Vol 1 5 001.jpg|250px|right|thumb|The Braddock Academy students fighting amongst themselves on [[Murderworld]]]]
While creating his newest death game, [[Arcade (Earth-616)|Arcade]] kidnapped five of the Braddock Academy's students including [[Aiden (Earth-616)|Anachronism]], [[Katy Bashir (Earth-616)|Apex]], [[Cullen Bloodstone (Earth-616)|Cullen Bloodstone]], [[Brian Braddock (Earth-13022)|Kid Briton]], and [[Nara (Earth-616)|Nara]]. After abducting the students, Arcade brought them to his new [[Murderworld|Murder World island]].{{r|Avengers Arena #1|#2}}

To prevent suspicion about their disappearance, Arcade periodically post fake picture and social media updates. Captain Britain has tried unsuccessfully to track his students, but instead has been left to clean their mess.{{r|Avengers Arena #13}}

The games began after Avengers Academy student [[Ken Mack (Earth-616)|Mettle]] sacrificed himself for his girlfriend [[Jennifer Takeda (Earth-616)|Hazmat]].{{r|Avengers Arena #1}} The Braddock Academy students ventured off by together and were soon joined by [[Rebecca Ryker (Earth-616)|Death Locket]].{{r|Avengers Arena #2}}

The Braddock Academy students suffered from internal conflict, which eventually resulted with Anachronism beheading Kid Briton,{{r|Avengers Arena Vol 1 6}} and Apex using her technopathy to attack all the other Murder World contents.{{r|Avengers Arena Vol 1 #8|#11}}

The three remaining students joined with [[Camille Benally (Earth-616)|Cammi]], the [[Runaways (Earth-616)|Runaways]], and [[Avengers Academy (Earth-616)|Avengers Academy students]].{{r|Avengers Arena Vol 1 #8|#15}} Ultimately, they were attacked by a rampaging [[Laura Kinney (Earth-616)|X-23]], and Cullen transformed into the Glartrox to fight her. Nara eventually sacrificed herself to save Cullen and prevent Aiden from murdering.{{r|Avengers Arena Vol 1 #15}}

===Contest of Champions===
Despite some truancy issues,{{r|Avengers Arena Vol 1 #1}}{{r|Avengers Arena Vol 1 #13}}{{r|Infinity: The Hunt #1}} the Braddock Academy was one of the many schools for super-powered adolescents to participate in the first annual Contest of Champions held at the [[Avengers Compound]] in [[Palo Alto]], [[California (State)|California]] under the direction of [[Meggan Puceanu (Earth-616)|Meggan]], [[Henry Pym (Earth-616)|Dr. Pym]], [[James Howlett (Earth-616)|Wolverine]], and [[Jennifer Walters (Earth-616)|She-Hulk]].{{r|Infinity: The Hunt #1}}

